{
  "id": "019cdffa-33ca-7711-81cc-c3c431242be4",
  "content": "# Dashboard Feature Roadmap (2026-03-12)\n\n## Context\nResearch into available corvia APIs revealed massive untapped surface: 30+ REST endpoints, 18 MCP tools, 16 OTEL span names. The standalone dashboard (tools/corvia-dashboard, Vite + Preact on port 8021) currently uses only 5 endpoints. This roadmap prioritizes features to make the dashboard world-class.\n\n## Tier 1 — High Impact, Low Effort (existing endpoints, zero backend changes)\n\n### 1. Agent Lifecycle Dashboard\n- Endpoints: `/api/agents`, `/api/agents/:id/sessions`, `/api/dashboard/status`\n- Live agent cards showing registration time, session count, last heartbeat\n- Session timeline per agent (created → committed → merged)\n- \"Who's active right now?\" at a glance\n\n### 2. Merge Queue Monitor\n- Endpoints: `/api/merge/queue`, `/api/merge/retry`, `/api/dashboard/status`\n- Real-time queue depth with entry-level detail (entry ID, conflict status, retry count, error messages)\n- One-click retry for failed merges directly from the dashboard\n- Conflict resolution history — which entries triggered LLM conflict resolution\n\n### 3. RAG Pipeline Trace Viewer\n- Endpoints: `/api/rag/context`, `/api/rag/ask`\n- Both return PipelineTrace with: retrieval duration, augmentation duration, generation duration, total tokens, context token budget\n- Waterfall visualization showing each RAG stage (retrieve → augment → generate)\n- Token budget utilization bar, side-by-side query/context/answer view\n- Most differentiated feature — no competing tool exposes RAG internals like this\n\n### 4. Knowledge Health Dashboard\n- Endpoint: `/api/reason/:scope`\n- Health checks: stale entries, broken supersession chains, orphaned entries, dangling graph edges, cycles\n- Traffic-light summary (green/yellow/red per check category)\n- Drill-down to specific problematic entries\n\n## Tier 2 — Medium Effort, High Differentiation\n\n### 5. Temporal History Explorer\n- Endpoints: `/api/history/:entry_id`, `/api/entries/:id`\n- Entry evolution timeline showing supersession chains\n- Diff view between versions, \"time travel\" slider\n\n### 6. Interactive Knowledge Graph\n- Endpoints: `/api/graph/edges/:scope`, `/api/graph/traverse`\n- Force-directed graph visualization (d3-force or similar)\n- BFS/DFS traversal from any node, shortest path between entries\n- Replace current flat edge table in GraphView\n\n### 7. Live Session State\n- Endpoints: `/api/agents/:id/sessions`, `/api/sessions/:id/entries`\n- Active staging sessions with uncommitted entries\n- Real-time \"what's being written right now\" feed\n\n## Tier 3 — Stretch Goals\n\n### 8. Configuration Control Panel\n- Editable config sidebar using `corvia_config_set` hot-reload\n- Toggle merge strategy, adjust token budgets, change log levels — all live\n\n### 9. OTEL Span Drill-Down\n- Span-level waterfall charts (parent→child span trees)\n- P50/P95/P99 latency percentiles, error rate sparklines\n\n### 10. GC Operations Dashboard\n- Trigger GC from dashboard with confirmation dialog\n- Show last GC run stats: entries swept, duration, space reclaimed\n\n## Recommended Build Order\n- Sprint 1: Merge Queue Monitor + Agent Lifecycle (3 new endpoints)\n- Sprint 2: RAG Pipeline Trace Viewer (2 new endpoints)\n- Sprint 3: Knowledge Health Dashboard (1 new endpoint)\n- Sprint 4: Interactive Knowledge Graph (2 new endpoints)\n- Sprint 5: Temporal History + Config Panel (3 new endpoints)\n\nFirst 3 sprints require zero backend changes — all APIs already exist.",
